description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Junior Sister / Charge Nurse to join our team on Ward 5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated, enthusiastic and innovative nurse to work and lead our team to help deliver high quality care to our patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ward 5 is a 21 bedded Endocrinology ward which specialises in the care of patients with diabetes and general medicine. The nursing team work closely with members of the multidisciplinary team and are keen to take forward and develop new innovations to enhance the patient experience. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an experienced nurse who can demonstrate their ability to support the team and ward manager, promote effective quality patient care and embrace daily challenges utilising appropriate clinical decision making. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will demonstrate excellent knowledge and previous experience of caring for patients as well as processing excellent leadership skills. You will be working collaboratively with other MDT members. You will be confident in working under your own initiative and able to prioritise your clinical care and work load accordingly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop your clinical skills and knowledge as well as enhancing your leadership and management skills with the full support of the ward manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be held on the 25th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
